#: src/administration/prometheus.md:1
msgid "Prometheus Metrics"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:3
msgid ""
"Lemmy supports the export of metrics in the [Prometheus](https://prometheus."
"io/) format. This document outlines how to enable the feature and begin "
"collecting metrics."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:7
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:9
msgid ""
"Configuration of the Prometheus endpoint is contained under the optional "
"`prometheus` object in the `lemmy.hjson` file. In this configuration block, "
"the `bind` address and `port` of the Prometheus metrics server can be "
"configured."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:13
msgid ""
"By default, it will serve on `127.0.0.1:10002`. If running inside a "
"container, it should instead bind on all addresses as below."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:16
msgid ""
"```\n"
"prometheus: {\n"
"  bind: \"0.0.0.0\"\n"
"  port: 10002\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:23
msgid "Scrape"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:25
msgid ""
"After Lemmy has been deployed, test that it is serving properly (substitute "
"the correct hostname if not running locally)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:32
msgid "Prometheus Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:34
msgid ""
"Below is a minimal configuration on the Prometheus server's side that will "
"scrape the metrics from Lemmy."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:38 src/administration/prometheus.md:57
msgid "global"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:38 src/administration/prometheus.md:57
msgid "scrape_configs"
msgstr ""

