msgid "targets"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:44
msgid "localhost:10002"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:47
msgid "Then run a Prometheus server to scrape the metrics."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:53
msgid ""
"If Lemmy was deployed using the `docker-compose.yml`, then use the following "
"configurations instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:63
msgid "lemmy:10002"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:66
msgid ""
"Run the Prometheus server inside the same docker network that Lemmy is "
"running in. This can be discovered by running `docker inspect` on the lemmy "
"container."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:73
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:75
msgid ""
"Below is an example of what is returned from the `/metrics` endpoint. Each "
"combination of `endpoint`, `method`, and `status` will produce a histogram "
"(`lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_*`), so for brevity the output "
"was reduced to a single endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:80
msgid ""
"For the HTTP metrics, this is saying that `/api/v3/post/list` received 12 "
"`GET` requests that returned a `200` HTTP code. Cumulatively, these requests "
"took 0.383 seconds. 5 requests completed between 0.01 and 0.025 seconds. 5 "
"more completed between 0.025 and 0.05 seconds. And the remaining 2 requests "
"completed between 0.05 and 0.1 seconds."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:86
msgid ""
"```\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.005\"} 0\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.01\"} 0\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.025\"} 5\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.05\"} 10\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.1\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.25\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"0.5\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"1\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"2.5\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"5\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"10\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_bucket{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\",le=\"+Inf\"} 12\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_sum{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/list\","
"method=\"GET\",status=\"200\"} 0.3834808429999999\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_duration_seconds_count{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/"
"list\",method=\"GET\",status=\"200\"} 12\n"
"\n"
"lemmy_api_http_requests_total{endpoint=\"/api/v3/post/list\",method=\"GET\","
"status=\"200\"} 12\n"
"\n"
"# HELP lemmy_db_pool_available_connections Number of available connections "
"in the pool\n"
"# TYPE lemmy_db_pool_available_connections gauge\n"
"lemmy_db_pool_available_connections 2\n"
"# HELP lemmy_db_pool_connections Current number of connections in the pool\n"
"# TYPE lemmy_db_pool_connections gauge\n"
"lemmy_db_pool_connections 2\n"
"# HELP lemmy_db_pool_max_connections Maximum number of connections in the "
"pool\n"
"# TYPE lemmy_db_pool_max_connections gauge\n"
"lemmy_db_pool_max_connections 5\n"
"\n"
"# HELP process_cpu_seconds_total Total user and system CPU time spent in "
"seconds.\n"
"# TYPE process_cpu_seconds_total counter\n"
"process_cpu_seconds_total 14\n"
"# HELP process_max_fds Maximum number of open file descriptors.\n"
"# TYPE process_max_fds gauge\n"
"process_max_fds 1073741816\n"
"# HELP process_open_fds Number of open file descriptors.\n"
"# TYPE process_open_fds gauge\n"
"process_open_fds 91\n"
"# HELP process_resident_memory_bytes Resident memory size in bytes.\n"
"# TYPE process_resident_memory_bytes gauge\n"
"process_resident_memory_bytes 75603968\n"
"# HELP process_start_time_seconds Start time of the process since unix epoch "
"in seconds.\n"
"# TYPE process_start_time_seconds gauge\n"
"process_start_time_seconds 1688487611\n"
"# HELP process_threads Number of OS threads in the process.\n"
"# TYPE process_threads gauge\n"
"process_threads 37\n"
"# HELP process_virtual_memory_bytes Virtual memory size in bytes.\n"
"# TYPE process_virtual_memory_bytes gauge\n"
"process_virtual_memory_bytes 206000128\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:137
msgid "Visualizing Metrics"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:139
msgid ""
"[Grafana](https://grafana.com/) can be used to visualize the metrics "
"collected by Prometheus. A community-maintained Grafana dashboard for Lemmy "
"is available on the Grafana dashboard registry."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:141
msgid ""
"Dashboard: [Lemmy – Grafana Dashboards](https://grafana.com/grafana/"
"dashboards/25020-lemmy/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:143
msgid ""
"Before importing the dashboard, add Prometheus as a data source in Grafana:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:145
msgid "In Grafana, go to **Connections** → **Data sources**."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:146
msgid "Click **Add new data source**, and select **Prometheus**."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:147
msgid ""
"Set the server URL to your Prometheus instance (e.g. `http://"
"localhost:10002`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:148
msgid "Click **Save & test** to confirm the connection."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:150
msgid "To use it:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:152
msgid "In your Grafana instance, go to **Dashboards** → **Import**."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:153
msgid "Enter the ID `25020` or paste the dashboard URL."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:154
msgid "Select your Prometheus data source and click **Import**."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/prometheus.md:156
msgid ""
"The dashboard provides an overview of HTTP request rates and latencies, "
"database connection pool usage, and process-level metrics such as CPU, "
"memory, and open file descriptors."
msgstr ""
